            <h1>Off The Record &bull; Record Club</h1>

            <h2 id="what">What's a record club?</h2>
            <p>We're still working it out ourselves, but <span class="otr">Off The Record</span> is be a monthly event where a bunch of music-loving people get together to listen to a couple of records in full &ndash; no distractions, no interruptions &ndash; and then talk about them afterwards.</p>

            <h2 id="where" class="header">Where and when does it happen?</h2>
            <p><span class="otr">Off The Record</span> is hosted by <a href="http://www.foodandfuel.co.uk/our-cafes/coco-momo-holborn/">Coco Momo cafe</a> in <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/64+Theobalds+Rd,+London+WC1X+8SF,+UK/@51.5207932,-0.1168255,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x48761b49fac08249:0xf8d7250f8348f9c7">central London</a>. It's an evening event, running from 7pm-9.30pm or so, with (so far) around 20 people attending. </p>

            <h2 id="suggest" class="header">Got a record to suggest?</h2>
            <p>Cool &ndash; we have <a href="#guidelines">some guidelines on hosting a playback / discussion</a> below. Have a read and you'll eventually be able to submit your record suggestion where people can vote for it for an upcoming <span class="otr">Off The Record</span> session. Or if you really can't wait, <a href="mailto:matt@mattandrews.info">email Matt</a> with your nominations.</p>

            <h2>Okay, I'm convinced, what next?</h2>
            <p>Great. <a href="http://attending.io/events/off-the-record-2/">Sign up to attend here</a>!</p>

        </article>
    </div>

